{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"muffin tray, refrigerator, oven","id":"r101787","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-yyKx7Xs61zU\/XZWfoA2hnsI\/AAAAAAAAfHk\/s6heNSCwikQOcGtteIr2xAFPKzd4uEKogCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ylND0a6CIyTMhti4.png","title":"Raspberry and Pistachio Muffins","publishedAt":"2016-05-09T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"65 g unsalted butter, soft"},{"content":"3 egg whites, from large eggs"},{"content":"1 pinch fine sea salt"},{"content":"80 g brown sugar"},{"content":"60 g pistachio nuts, unsalted, shelled, plus 2 Tbsp for decoration"},{"content":"50 g ground almonds"},{"content":"30 g cornflour"},{"content":"1 tsp baking powder"},{"content":"100 g fresh raspberries, halved"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"7 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"1045 kJ \/ 249 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Grease 4 holes of a muffin tin with 15 g butter and set aside."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place 2 egg whites and salt in mixing bowl then whisk <b>5 min\/speed 3.5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Rinse mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place brown sugar and pistachio nuts in mixing bowl then grind <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>."},{"content":"Add ground almonds, remaining 50 g butter, cornflour, remaining egg white and baking powder then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Fold mixture into reserved egg whites using spatula.  Stir in 100 g raspberries using spatula then divide amongst 4 greased muffin holes, up to 1 cm from the top. Sprinkle remaining 2 Tbsp unsalted, shelled pistachios over the tops. Allow muffins to rest in fridge for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C."},{"content":"Bake for 25 minutes (180°C). Leave to cool before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["It is important the mixing bowl and butterfly whisk are very clean when whisking egg whites.","Vary the flavour with the seasons - hazelnut and pears, almond and cherry, coconut and pineapple."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","55m","4 portions"]}